Author-Name: Pranab Bardhan
Author-Name: Dilip Mookherjee
Title: Determinants of Redistributive Politics: An Empirical Analysis of Land Reforms in West Bengal, India
Abstract: We investigate political determinants of land reform implementation in the
Indian state of West Bengal. Using a village panel spanning 1974-1998, we do
not find evidence supporting the hypothesis that land reforms were positively and monotonically related to control of local governments by a Left Front coalition vis-&agrave;-vis the right-centrist Congress party, combined with lack of commitment to policy platforms. Instead, the evidence is consistent with a quasi-Downsian theory stressing the role of opportunism (reelection concerns) and electoral competition. (JEL D72, O13, O17, Q15)
